<taxonomicName id="59CA4D29FFF0FFDE9BC1FA74FE486FA2" authorityName="Medvedev &amp; Dang" authorityYear="1981" box="[151,455,1439,1463]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="721" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF0FFDE9BC1FA74FE486FA2" bold="true" box="[151,455,1439,1463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF0FFDE9BC1FA74FEF66FA2" bold="true" box="[151,377,1439,1463]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">Hesperopenna minor</emphasis>
group.
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6D06521FFF0FFDE9A9DFA74FEC66C02" pageId="6" pageNumber="721" type="description">
<paragraph id="9E7536AAFFF0FFDE9A9DFA74FEC66C02" blockId="6.[149,1127,1439,1623]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">
Body length 3.2 
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF0FFDE9938FA74FDF46FA2" bold="true" box="[622,635,1439,1463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">–</emphasis>
5.0 mm. Body completely orange.Antennomere III about 1.3–1.5 times longer than anntenomere II. Pronotum transverse, 1.6 
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF0FFDE988EFA54FC6A6FC2" bold="true" box="[984,997,1471,1495]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">–</emphasis>
2.2 times as wide as long, covered with fine dense punctures. Elytra glabrous. Aedeagus relatively short, simple (
<figureCitation id="06F12A2FFFF0FFDE9BBBFA14FEB26C02" box="[237,317,1535,1559]" captionStart="Figs 66–69" captionStartId="26.[151,188,1519,1538]" captionTargetBox="[216,1055,416,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-45@26.[207,1071,413,1499]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 66–69.Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; ventral view). 66 – Hesperopenna vietnamica (Medvedev, 2000) (paratype); 67 – H. antennalis (Kimoto, 1989); 68 – H. minor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype); 69 – H. bicolor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740073/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6D06521FFF0FFDE9BE3F9F4FEFC6C42" pageId="6" pageNumber="721" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9E7536AAFFF0FFDE9BE3F9F4FEFC6C42" blockId="6.[149,1127,1439,1623]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF0FFDE9BE3F9F4FEF46C22" bold="true" box="[181,379,1567,1591]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="59CA4D29FFF0FFDE9AD2F9CBFC956C22" authority="(Kimoto, 1989)" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Kimoto" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[388,794,1567,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="721" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF0FFDE9AD2F9CBFDE76C22" box="[388,616,1568,1591]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">Hesperopenna minor</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FA5B4B5BFFF0FFDE992FF9F4FC9C6C22" author="KIMOTO S." box="[633,787,1567,1591]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721" pagination="1 - 241" refId="ref15334" refString="KIMOTO S. 1989: Chrysomelidae (Coleoptera) of Thailand, Cambodia, Laos and Vietnam. IV. Galerucinae. Esakia 27: 1 - 241." type="journal article" year="1989">Kimoto, 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(comb. nov.) and at least two undescribed species.
</paragraph>
